"This is the situation. I encountered a issue that had no problems previously with my Motorcycle for the last dozen years. Starting from a dead stop at a stop ir a light my Motorcycle begins to buck or hesitate violently. The more I press the throttle it begins to move faster. A normal stomp of the throttle on the deck will be met with an angry roar which is is not normal. It may be ridden as it is, but no longer give dependable acceleration. Or you can smell the bike burning out. The fully warmed up engine does not do this but sometimes revs are limited to 3500 rpm until then at start up any throttle command will cause an un-provable violent buck. Then who ever happened to be sitting on the bike begins to describe there short jolting ride at light stop.I
